The experience begins upon application. Absolutely zero responses to my emails for several years. There doesn't seem to be any ticket management.  There are lots of names and domain names at this university: u-paris.fr, parisdescartes.fr, Paris Cit√©, Paris V, etc.  The organization, seen from the outside, is a real artifice to me, like your public information broken down into your multiple domain names. I am carrying out a search related to your university and, systematically, I cannot find an up-to-date answer and answer. This experiment was repeated several times, always with the same result. Sometimes your site states the opposite of what the facts are. This is how your site indicates valid training which is not communicated on your e-candidate platform; disturbing for the student.  This is problematic: it is impossible to contact the training managers by email. Either they are ghosting or they are not receiving or transmitting to me. As I imagine myself as a student at your university, I tell myself that everyday life must be just as problematic, if not more problematic.  Lack of viability, at least at first glance.

I signed up for DU Naps and I don't recommend it to everyone. The administrative service is most astonishing. Since September I have been fighting to benefit from my courses for which I paid 1000 euros. It's April and not only did I not have access to it but they had the nerve to unsubscribe me through total incompetence. They are completely unreachable by phone and email. I was supposed to study for an exam. I have never seen such a display of administrative incompetence which for me amounted to theft, I lost 1000 euros. Thank you so much.
